text: Nawel Chiali (born 28 June 1991) is an Algerian rower. She competed in the 2018 World Rowing Championships held in Plovdiv, Bulgaria. She competed in rowing at the 2019 African Games held in Rabat, Morocco. She won the gold medal in the women's single sculls 500 metres event.
